cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) in the medical domain, specifically abbreviation disambiguation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also proposes a novel data augmentation technique, which involves generating new data from related medical concepts, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of global context information, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) or neural networks (cs.NE).
